Feature: on a version-tag release, each framework-utility repo emits a repository_dispatch to the bc-launcher build workflow

  Pins ADR-021 D2 (cross-repo auto-rebuild, trigger-EMIT side). A
  "framework-utility release" is a version-tag push on a utility repo (the
  scenario-129 / scenario-142 release convention). On such a release, the utility
  repo's release workflow fires a "repository_dispatch" event at the
  shopsystem-bc-launcher repository — the inbound signal scenario 38 rebuilds on.
  Each utility carries one small emit step; the build authority stays in
  bc-launcher.

  One Scenario per utility repo so each names a concrete target the Architect can
  tag and route. bc-launcher's own release is NOT covered here — its own
  same-repo tag trigger (scenario 37) is its rebuild reason.

  Scenario: on a version-tag release of shopsystem-messaging, its release workflow emits a repository_dispatch to the bc-launcher repository
    Given the shopsystem-messaging source repository
    And a tag named "v0.2.0" is pushed to its "main" branch
    When the shopsystem-messaging release workflow associated with that tag push runs to successful completion
    Then the workflow performs a "repository_dispatch" API call targeting the "shopsystem-bc-launcher" repository
    And that dispatch call carries a credential authorized to dispatch to the bc-launcher repository

  Scenario: on a version-tag release of shopsystem-scenarios, its release workflow emits a repository_dispatch to the bc-launcher repository
    Given the shopsystem-scenarios source repository
    And a tag named "v0.2.0" is pushed to its "main" branch
